        "timestamp": "2018-03-21 18:31:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLiam, I just checked with the original developer, Ali Hockla. There was no in progress messages. There should not be a request embedded in the response, the original archetype so response is correct. I'm adding Ali so he could provide more information.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "943847be304e88109ef3462a32685ee5ecec5b24",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1757,
          "name": "Ali Hockla",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ah999m@att.com",
          "username": "ah999m"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-21 20:12:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Liam, I just checked with the original developer, Ali Hockla. There\n > was no in progress messages. There should not be a request embedded\n > in the response, the original archetype so response is correct. I'm\n > adding Ali so he could provide more information.\n\n@Pam, here is a sample SO response:\n{\n    \"requestReferences\": {\n        \"instanceId\": \"ff305d54-75b4-ff1b-bdb2-eb6b9e5460ff\",\n        \"requestId\": \"e4f95e0c-a013-4530-8e59-c5c5f9e539b6\"\n    },\n    \"httpResponseCode\": 200\n}\n\nDan is correct. There is no 'in progress' message sent by SO. This is the only response they send.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e7845882eeec04316243be32c4904a2bde34f351",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2787,
          "name": "Liam Fallon",
